Hints
=====

   Solutions and hints for many popular games are available via
anonymous ftp at @{b}ftp://risc.ua.edu/pub/games/solutions@{ub} and
@{b}ftp.uu.net/pub/games/solutions@{ub}. There's also a large solution site at
@{b}ftp://nic.funet.fi/pub/doc/games/solutions@{ub}, but you will need unzip or
gzip to uncompress these files.  (Avaliable on @{i}Aminet@{ui} as
@{b}/util/arc/unzip51x.lha@{ub} and @{b}/util/pack/gzip124x2.lha@{ub})

   @{i}Aminet@{ui} has hints in the @{b}/game/hint@{ub} directory.

   There is also the @{i}Games Domain@{ui} site which has walkthroughs for
several popular games at @{b}http://wcl-rs.bham.ac.uk/GamesDomain@{ub}.

   Most Amiga @{"Magazines" Link "Magazines"} publish walkthru's for new games.

   A new web site with most known cheats is available over the web -
http://www.netrover.com/~timt/amicheats.html.

   If you can't find an answer there, post your question-chances are
@{i}somebody@{ui} on comp.sys.amiga.games has gotten farther than you!

   If someone posts a question for which you also want the answer,
instead of posting "Send me the answer too!" send email to the original
poster and ask him or her to relay the answer to you.


