Archivers
=========

   DMS files are packed with the DiskMasher.  This packs whole disks
and is the main way to distribute Non-DOS disks over the internet.  A
copy of DMS can be found on Aminet as @{b}/util/arc/dms111.run@{ub}.  To undms
to a disk in df0: type @{b}dms WRITE file.dms TO df0:@{ub}.  @{i}DMS files are now
banned from Aminet.@{ui}  For reasons, see the file@{b}docs/misc/dms-sucks.txt@{ub}.

   LHA and LZH files are packed with an LHA compatible packer.  The
main one is LHA which is shareware.  A freeware alternative is LZ.
Both of these are on Aminet as @{b}/util/arc/LhA_e138.run@{ub} and
@{b}/util/arc/lz_1.92.lzh@{ub} (this needs LHA to unpack it however so you'll
have to get LHA ...).  To unlha to a formatted disk in df0: type @{b}lha -a
x file.lha df0:@{ub}.

   The dms and lha archives are self-extracting files so executing them
will leave you with the appropriate files.


